Median: you put your list of ten numbers in order from smallest to biggest. The number in the middle of that list is the median. The median number will exist in the original list.
Mean: you have a list of (for example) ten numbers. You add them all together, then divide the result by ten. That result is the mean. Whether that number exists in the list doesn't matter here.
